syllabus:
Course Description:

This course aims to teach students: 1. Understanding important issues in multicultural counseling. 2. Increase the learners' multicultural self-awareness. 3. Understanding of multicultural counseling and specific ethnic groups and practical issues. 4. Cultivate the knowledge of multicultural counseling and practical work. 5. Learn the work ethics of multicultural populations.

Course Objective:

*   Understand how a person is shaped by society and culture;
*   Have multicultural counseling competency;
*   Understand multicultural counseling techniques and methods;
*   Understand the social and cultural context carried out by multicultural counseling;
*   Understand multicultural specific ethnic groups and counseling;
*   Understand multicultural counseling ethics;
*   Gain understanding and knowledge on how critical cultural factors affect’s people’s relationship building, and conflict resolution, and mental health human behavior;
*   Acquire ample exposures to various Western cultural perspectives and values via a safe and constructively challenging environment;
*   Enhance adaptability to international learning environment and ability to effectively copy with challenges during cross-cultural transitions;
*   Facilitate the transformation of students’ knowledge into cross-cultural sensitivity and skills via collaborating with UNT students to complete team projects.
